=Description=

"The complementary currency (cc) Research Group is a network of researchers - academic and non-academic - working on complementary currency systems and related types of appropriate and sustainable exchange systems.

The purpose of the ccResearch Group is to enable peer support and collaboration for researchers across institutions and disciplines.

If you are searching for information about complementary currencies in general, please turn to the CC Knowledge Gateway and the social media channels linked from there.

The group was originally proposed and hosted by Stephen DeMeulenaere of the "CC Resource Center". Since 2014 the group has been moderated by Leander Bindewald and hosted courtesy of the New Economics Foundation (nef) and the Community Currencies in Action (CCIA) EU Interreg project."
(http://forum.community-currency.info/sign_in)


